We are looking for a developer who has experience working with frontend technologies such as React.js and Next.js who will work on the frontend code for websites that may work with web2 and web3 technologies. You will strive to achieve and maintain high performance and responsiveness, prioritizing the responsiveness of the web app to our users and stakeholders in the team.
While the back-end elements will be developed by your co-workers from another team, you will be responsible for their integration into the overall project. So you will work closely with the backend engineers to ensure that the web app is integrated well.

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES
Developing user-facing applications using Next.js and Tailwind CSS
Building modular and reusable components and libraries
Optimizing your application for performance
Implementing automated testing integrated into development and maintenance workflows
Staying up-to-date with all recent developments in the Next.js and React.js space

Proposing any upgrades and updates necessary for keeping up with modern security and development best practices

3+ years of Next.js experience;
Highly proficient with React and TypeScript syntax;
Familiarity with Next.js and the Vercel ecosystem
Good understanding of Tailwind CSS;
Understanding of SSG and SSR and its use cases;
Ability to write efficient, secure, well-documented, modular and clean JavaScript code
Familiarity with automated JavaScript testing such as Javascript Testing Library and Playwright/Cypress is a bonus.
Experience with both RESTful and GraphQL APIs

MUST HAVE:
Adaptability in a SME / startup environment
Communication and presentation skills, high interpersonal skills.
Abilities to set achievable and measurable personal goals for performance and growth, and juggle multiple competing dead-lines.
A growth mindset and desire to continually learn and share new techniques and ideas
A passion for fintech and blockchain related technologies

WHY WORK FOR US
Be part of the journey to build one of the world’s earliest DAO from the ground up.
Great culture: highly professional and ambitious, yet informal, friendly, non-hierarchical, collaborative, and entrepreneurial.
Business is backed by top-tiered VC and Industry leaders such as Animoca Brands.
Work with the best talents in Crypto, highly experienced executive, and advisor teams.
Best place to learn crypto, and work with a high-performing team on the cutting edge of blockchain technology.

Collaborate with our AI/back-end dev and tech lead to build slick, user-friendly interfaces using React, JavaScript, HTML, and CSS.

Are you a highly skilled freelance Frontend Developer with a passion for tackling exciting, impactful projects? Are you looking to expand your opportunities while retaining the freedom and flexibility that freelance work provides? We’d love to hear from you!

We are looking for freelance Frontend Developers who

Have hands-on experience in building modern web applications using frameworks such as Angular, React or Vue.js.
Are adept at developing highly responsive, dynamic user interfaces with HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript and TypeScript.
Possess skills in integrating RESTful APIs and managing state using tools like Redux, MobX, NgRx or similar.
Have experience working in agile environments and collaborating with cross-functional teams.
Possess strong communication skills and thrive in remote project setups.
Stay updated on the latest frontend technologies, trends and best practices in UI/UX development.

How it works

When an opportunity that aligns with your skills and interests arises, we’ll notify you and present the project.

Excellent English skills are mandatory, as it is our primary language for communication, documentation and collaboration. German language skills are a plus and may open additional opportunities in german-speaking projects.
Several years of experience is required to ensure candidates have the expertise to manage projects independently and deliver high-quality results.
To ensure seamless collaboration, time-zone compatibility and adherence to regional standards such as the NIS2 Directive on cybersecurity and data protection, we can only consider applications from freelancers based in Europe.

Title: Frontend Developer (React) (m/f/d)
About Job:
About the job
Environment

JustRelate is a software vendor based in France, Germany, and Poland specializing in digital solutions for 650 customers - all B2B, such as large enterprises and the public sector. 200 teammates develop and sell various SaaS offerings to create comprehensive customer engagement platforms, including CRM, DXP, Marketing Automation, and Email Builder software.

Mission

We are looking for a React Frontend Developer for projects based on our next-generation multi-tenancy SaaS platform. In our projects we work for mid-sized to large enterprises, with ease of use, scalability, and extensibility in mind.

Responsibilities

You design and develop customized Web Applications in a test-driven way for our customers based on our SaaS platform.
You tailor our highly flexible standard software to meet specific requirements and integrate it seamlessly into the existing IT and process landscape.
You provide our customers with comprehensive support, take part in Scrum Meetings, analyze requirements and business processes and assist them in successfully utilizing our solutions over the long term.

Technical Skills

At least 2 years of professional experience in the field of development and optimization of interactive web applications based on ReactJS and/or TypeScript
Experience with using and providing web services APIs, especially with REST and GraphQL
Understanding of HTML, CSS and optional also with modern frameworks such as Bootstrap or Foundation
Experience with working in NodeJS will be considered a strong plus

Personal Qualities

Strong German and English knowledge: Even though at JustRelate we're English-first, you'll be mostly working with German speaking customers.
Creativity: You think innovatively and bring fresh ideas to the design process.
Attention to Detail: You strive for precision and consistency in all design aspects.
Empathy: You have a deep understanding of the user’s needs, motivations and pain points.
Collaboration: You're a strong team player and communicator who can work seamlessly with cross-functional teams and Customers.
Problem-Solving Skills: You address design challenges and find practical, user-centered solutions.
Time Management: You're capable of handling multiple projects and meeting deadlines without compromising on quality.
Autonomy: Ability to self-motivate, take responsibility, inspire teammates and other colleagues

What we offer

Mentor-accompanied onboarding in the job.
In-depth familiarisation with the area of responsibility.
A very broad field of further development opportunities.
Plenty of room for personal initiative and creativity.
A secure workplace with a high feel-good factor.
Flexible working hours and a family-friendly working atmosphere.
Provision of modern work equipment.
Remote working is always possible, but we also have smart offices.
30 days holiday.
Regular company events like Christmas Party and Summer Party.
An open corporate culture.

If you’re passionate about crafting seamless, user-focused web experiences and have a solid grasp of the underlying code, we’d love to hear from you! Join us to make a real impact on how our users interact with our web applications.

Our client is a well-established e-commerce brand in the home and lifestyle sector, offering a broad range of innovative products. Their online platform allows consumers to purchase high-quality lifestyle solutions quickly and efficiently. With a commitment to sustainability and customer satisfaction, they aim to enhance everyday life through practical and stylish product offerings. This role presents an exciting opportunity to play a key part in optimizing digital performance and enhancing the customer journey. As a Website Optimisation Manager (CRO) you will be responsible for increasing conversion rates across multiple websites within the group, driving data-driven improvements, and collaborating with design and development teams to implement impactful changes.


Role Description
We’re looking for a CRO Manager to join our client’s team. If you're an analytical and results-driven professional with a passion for website optimization and data-backed decision-making, this could be the opportunity you’ve been looking for. You’ll take ownership of conversion rate optimization efforts, oversee testing programs, and lead strategic initiatives to enhance user experience and site performance.
This position offers significant opportunities for personal and professional growth within a dynamic and fast-paced e-commerce environment.

CRO Strategy & Execution – Develop and implement a comprehensive CRO strategy to enhance website conversion rates and overall user experience.

Stakeholder Communication – Present findings and recommendations to senior stakeholders, ensuring CRO initiatives align with broader business goals.

Technical & UX Knowledge – Understanding of UX principles, website functionality, and front-end development constraints.
Communication & Collaboration – Excellent English communication skills, with the ability to work effectively across teams and present complex insights in an accessible way.


Company Benefits
Top-of-the-market pay.
Remote working.
Potential for flexible hours.
Becoming a part of Palm Outsourcing, where your performance is rewarded in long-term job security and continued growth opportunities.

This is a fantastic opportunity for a CRO professional to make a direct impact on an e-commerce brand’s success while working in a collaborative and growth-focused environment.

Thank you for taking the time to apply, we look forward to reviewing your application.

Title: Frontend Developer (React)
About Job:
About the job
Puesto: Front end developer (React).
Ubicación: Madrid, España. Híbrido.
Salario: [35k-45k]
Perks: horario muy flexible, seguro médico gratuito, gimnasio/wellness, descuento empleado en flota de coches.

¿Qué es REVEL? 🚗

REVEL es una startup que busca revolucionar la manera de tener un coche. Damos la posibilidad de tener un coche con todos los servicios incluidos de una manera mucho más sencilla, flexible y conveniente que el resto de soluciones, contratando 100% online a través de nuestra web (https://driverevel.com/).

El equipo de REVEL lo formamos gente con experiencia en negocios digitales, tecnología y finanzas, que en el pasado ya hemos creado, escalado y vendido otras startups, y ahora queremos revolucionar el mundo de la movilidad con REVEL. 

Además, tenemos la suerte de estar respaldados por inversores reputados y recientemente hemos anunciado una ronda de financiación de 115 millones de euros participada por el fondo de inversión internacional KKR y el Banco Santander, entre otros.

¿Qué estamos buscando? 👀

En REVEL buscamos a un frontend Developer Javascript que quiera unirse a nuestro equipo de desarrollo.
Queremos que la tecnología sea uno de los motores de nuestro crecimiento. Para ello estamos incorporando perfiles como el tuyo en nuestro equipo.
Colaborarás con un equipo de desarrolladores multidisciplinar en un entorno ágil para crear soluciones software que generen valor dentro de la compañía.
Podrás colaborar con nuestros equipos de producto y operaciones para traducir los objetivos de negocio en retos para el equipo de tecnología.

Proyectarás pruebas de concepto con las que poner a prueba nuevas ideas.
Además de la web transaccional que puedes visitar, tenemos muchos otros desarrollos interesantes y variados: sistemas de gestión y monitorización de flota en tiempo real, landings comerciales, una app para nuestros clientes…

Requisitos Indispensables:
Tienes al menos 3 años de experiencia en un puesto similar.
Valores como la atención al detalle, proactividad y "ownership". El encaje cultural es casi más importante que el técnico en nuestra compañía :)
Te apasiona crear software.
Te manejas con soltura en Javascript y Typescript.
Estás familiarizado con el desarrollo web en React (usamos Nextjs)

Suma puntos:
Tienes side projects interesantes.
Has trabajado antes en el mundo startup.
Tienes un buen nivel de inglés. Trabajamos con partners internacionales.
Cualquier otra tecnología / plataforma con la que tengas experiencia y que quieras compartir.

¿Localización? 🏢

Este rol y los REVELers con los que interactuará más recurrentemente, tienen su base en Madrid, en nuestras oficinas de Carrera de San Jerónimo. La verdad es que en REVEL nos gusta ir a la oficina, pero siempre que sea necesario, más conveniente o se te antoje trabajar en otro lugar durante unos días, no hay ningún problema en trabajar desde allá donde estés.

Qué te ofrecemos 🤗

REVEL es actualmente una de las empresas de mayor crecimiento en España, con un aumento exponencial en nuestra base de clientes. Además, contamos con un ambiente perfecto para que crees verdadero impacto: ganas de ofrecer colectivamente el mejor producto a clientes junto a responsabilidad individual de cada empleado en su área.

Un entorno ágil donde tus opiniones importan y se materializan, de hecho esperamos que opines y nos ayudes a definir juntos nuestro proyecto.
Formato híbrido en nuestra oficina de Madrid con flexibilidad horaria REAL, trabajamos orientado a resultados.
Revisiones de performance y condiciones periódicas.

Salario y perks:
Salario bruto anual en la horquilla: [35k-45k]
Seguro médico privado gratuito de primer nivel.
Gimnasio y fitness gratis con Wellhub (antiguo Gympass). Acceso gratuito a miles de centros fitness: yoga, boxeo, escalada…
Precio superreducido para empleados en nuestra flota de coches.
23 días laborable de vacaciones + tu cumpleaños libre.
Remuneración flexible a través de Payflow. 
Acceso a toda la red de coworkings de Spaces en el mundo.

¿Cómo trabajamos?
En REVEL trabajamos con sprints cortos, con objetivos medibles y con requisitos claros. Esto nos permite organizar el trabajo de una forma eficiente.
Intentamos ponerle cariño a todo lo que hacemos, por lo que la atención al detalle y la responsabilidad sobre nuestro trabajo son factores fundamentales en nuestra forma de trabajar.

¿Cómo será el proceso? ⚙️

El proceso consta de varias fases:

Tendremos una entrevista personal corta donde nos conoceremos mutuamente. Allí podrás contarnos tu experiencia previa y hacernos las preguntas que quieras. Durará una media hora.
Si a ambas partes nos encaja, haremos un proceso técnico a los pocos días. Este proceso puede ser una prueba técnica o una entrevista técnica en profundidad. Puedes incluso presentar un proyecto que ya hayas desarrollado si crees que está al nivel. En definitiva, queremos ver código y comentarlo.
Te plantearemos algunos escenarios hipotéticos y nos gustaría escuchar como los abordarías en detalle.
Si llegas a la fase final, te invitaremos a tomar un café con el equipo para conocernos en una charla distendida.

La duración de todo el proceso no será mayor a 2 semanas
